cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I like a weak 2@D because it comes up much more often. But mini-roman, when it comes up, can work well. The problem is it only comes up like 2% of the time, whereas you get to open a weak 2@D much more often. I believe, in general, you should gear your bidding to the hand types that come up more frequently.|
PG| ***** 83 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The best example of a convention based on frequency is the negative double. Yes, every once in a while you would like to have the penalty double available after an overcall. But the negative double comes up so much more frequently that it is much better to give up rare penalty doubles in favor of frequent negative doubles.|
PG| ***** 84 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So that is what you should do in general. Play those conventions that help you with the common hands. Don't worry about the esoteric hands. They rarely come up. If you bid the common hands correctly, you will do much better than most people.|
