NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|For example, take the auction 1@C-1N-2@H. The 2@H is to play, not forcing. That is a rare case where a new suit by responder is not forcing. If the 2@H bidder had a good hand, they should double. The auction 1@D-1@H-1N-2@S is similar. If Todd had a good hand he could double. So new suits after a NT overcall or natural bid are not forcing. they are to play. But in general new suits by responder and advancer (responder to overcaller) are forcing.|
